---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/ui/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { capabilities, observables, antiPatterns, playbooks, calibrationSignals, rubricAnchors, evidenceTypes, interviewQuestions, learningPathways, careerLevels } from '../lib/data';
import { url } from '../lib/url';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About the Engineering Leadership Matrix v6 — methodology, structure, and how to use it.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
    <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'About' }]} />

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight mb-6">About the Matrix</h1>

    <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">What is the Engineering Leadership Matrix?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          The Engineering Leadership Matrix v6 is a unified capability model for engineering managers and directors at Big Tech companies. It provides a structured, evidence-based framework for career development, performance calibration, and leadership growth.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Structure</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">The matrix is organized into interconnected layers:</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">{capabilities.length}</div>
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Capabilities</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Core competency areas across 6 domains</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">{observables.length}</div>
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Observables</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Specific behaviors you can measure</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">{antiPatterns.length}</div>
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Anti-Patterns</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Common failure modes to watch for</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">{playbooks.length}</div>
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Playbooks</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Scenario-based decision frameworks</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">{calibrationSignals.length}</div>
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Calibration Signals</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Language for promo packets & reviews</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">{interviewQuestions.length}</div>
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Interview Questions</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Behavioral, situational, and technical</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-4">
          <strong>Coverage %</strong> indicates the percentage of a capability's primary sub-topics that are represented by at least one observable. A higher coverage percentage means more of the capability's conceptual scope is measurable through specific behaviors.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Domains</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Capabilities are organized into 6 domains:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-blue-500"></span><span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Strategy</span> — Org-level thinking, prioritization, resource allocation</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span><span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Execution</span> — Systems design, operational rhythm, delivery</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-purple-500"></span><span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Stakeholder</span> — Decision framing, cross-functional influence</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-amber-500"></span><span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">People</span> — Coaching, hiring, culture, performance management</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500"></span><span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Reliability</span> — Incidents, risk, security, compliance</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-cyan-500"></span><span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Data</span> — Metrics, measurement, outcomes</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Use</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li><strong>Self-assessment:</strong> Use the <a href={url("/rubric/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Rubric</a> to evaluate your current level across capabilities.</li>
          <li><strong>1:1 conversations:</strong> Use capability pages and observables to structure feedback conversations.</li>
          <li><strong>Career planning:</strong> Identify capabilities to develop and use evidence types to track progress.</li>
          <li><strong>Promo packets:</strong> Use <a href={url("/calibration/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">calibration signals</a> as language templates.</li>
          <li><strong>Scenario prep:</strong> Use <a href={url("/playbooks/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">playbooks</a> to prepare for common leadership scenarios.</li>
          <li><strong>Anti-pattern recognition:</strong> Use <a href={url("/anti-patterns/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">anti-patterns</a> to identify and correct failure modes early.</li>
          <li><strong>Learning pathways:</strong> Follow <a href={url("/learning-pathways/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">curated learning resources</a> organized by capability — foundational, practical, and advanced.</li>
          <li><strong>Interactive self-rating:</strong> Use the <a href={url("/self-assessment/tool/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">interactive self-assessment tool</a> to rate yourself across all capabilities and identify gaps.</li>
          <li><strong>Interview prep:</strong> Use <a href={url("/interview-questions/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">{interviewQuestions.length} interview questions</a> with follow-ups, green flags, and red flags.</li>
          <li><strong>Career progression:</strong> Understand <a href={url("/career-progression/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">scope, expectations, and transition signals</a> for EM through VP levels.</li>
          <li><strong>Org maturity:</strong> Assess your engineering organization's <a href={url("/org-maturity/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">maturity level</a> from Ad Hoc to Optimizing.</li>
          <li><strong>Measurement:</strong> Use the <a href={url("/measurement-guide/")} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">measurement guide</a> for leading/lagging indicators and anti-patterns per capability.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Version History</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Version 6 represents the latest iteration of the matrix, with fixes for anti-pattern alignment, reconciled observable counts, updated EM relevance ratings, and coverage percentages.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
